============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Golden Ratio
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = 1.618...
Applications: Art, architecture, nature, design
Discoverer:   Ancient Greeks (500)

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Renaissance?
A1: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q2: What is quantum mechanics?
A2: Quantum mechanics describes physics at atomic and
     subatomic scales. Key principles: wave-particle
     duality, uncertainty principle, superposition, and
     quantum entanglement.

Q3: What is photosynthesis?
A3: Photosynthesis converts sunlight, CO2, and water into
     glucose and oxygen: 6CO2 + 6H2O + light → C6H12O6 +
     6O2. It occurs in plant chloroplasts.

Q4: What is capitalism?
A4: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q5: What is machine learning?
A5: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

